Vice President Mike Pence spoke with President Ivan Duque of Colombia to emphasize the strong relationship between the two countries. They discussed the humanitarian crisis in Venezuela and the impact it is having on the region. Both leaders expressed their commitment to maintaining pressure on the Maduro regime and addressing the collapse of democracy in Venezuela. Pence also praised Duque's efforts in the fight against illegal drugs and highlighted it as a priority going forward. They also talked about the upcoming United Nations General Assembly and opportunities for economic and trade engagement.